iety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/ |archivedate=March 15, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/saturn-awards-winners-2018-black-panther/ |work=Collider |first=Adam |last=Chitwood | title=\u2018Black Panther\u2019 Tops Saturn Awards with Five Wins; \u2018The Last Jedi\u2019 Takes Best Screenplay|date=June 28, 2018 |access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Mirojnick, Ellen\" | Ellen Mirojnick\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Music|Best Music]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Debney, John\" | [[John Debney]] and [[Joseph Trapanese]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"9\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"9\"| [[2018 Teen Choice Awards|August 12, 2018]]\n| Choice Breakout Movie Star\n| data-sort-value=\"Settle, Keala\" | [[Keala Settle]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Douglas |first1=Esme |title=Teen Choice Awards 2018: See the full list of winners |url=https://ew.com/awards/2018/08/12/teen-choice-awards-winners-list/ |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=August 13, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813151232/https://ew.com/awards/2018/08/12/teen-choice-awards-winners-list/ |archivedate=August 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music \u2013 Collaboration|Choice Collaboration]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Rewrite the Stars\" | \"Rewrite the Stars\" \u2013 Zac Efron and Zendaya\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie \u2013 Drama|Choice Drama Movie]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Greatest Showman, The\" | ''The Greatest Showman''\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Choice Drama Movie Actor\n| data-sort-value=\"Efron, Zac\" | [[Zac Efron]]\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Jackman, Hugh\" | Hugh Jackman\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Choice Drama Movie Actress\n| Zendaya\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Choice Liplock\n| data-sort-value=\"Efron, Zac\" | Zac Efron and Zendaya\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Ship\n| data-sort-value=\"Efron, Zac\" | Zac Efron and Zendaya\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Choice Pop Song\n| data-sort-value=\"This Is Me\" | \"This Is Me\" \u2013 Keala Settle\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[Barnum (musical)|Barnum]]'', 1980 Broadway show with music by Cy Coleman\n* ''[[The Greatest Show on Earth (film)|The Greatest Show on Earth]]'', 1952 film directed by Cecil B. DeMille\n* [[Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey Circus]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{AllRovi title}}\n* {{Mojo title}}\n* {{Metacritic film}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes}}\n* [http://www.historyvshollywood.com/reelfaces/greatest-showman/ ''The Greatest Showman''] at ''[[History vs. Hollywood]]''\n\n{{Barnum}}\n{{Bill Condon}}\n{{Teen Choice Award Choice Movie Drama}}\n{{Saturn Award for Best Action or Adventure Film}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Greatest Showman, The}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American biographical films]]\n[[Category:American musical drama films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox films]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about entertainers]]\n[[Category:Films about playwrights]]\n[[Category:Circus films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films scored by John Debney]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Joseph Trapanese]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Peter Chernin]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Laurence Mark]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Bill Condon]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of P. T. Barnum]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Jenny Lind]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Queen Victoria on film]]\n[[Category:Musical film